Phrase: Then... After considerable difficulty, we've succeeded in defeating the huge monster at the end of a fierce battle. The monster was controlled by Fussen as per her plan, a railway line was laid - and we escaped to the surface.
At the same time, dawn greets the night, and under brilliant sunshine -- Everyone rejoiced at the victory, the successful escape, and the reunion.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Hawawa, it was a really bad time!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Yeah... This time we didn't do anything from the beginning to the end, so stressful. I went to bed and woke up and it was all over - plus I had the worst nightmare during that time.

The girls who were rescued from inside the body of the defeated monster kept complaining about it. Apparently, the monster had a habit of capturing small spiders under its control, or those that wandered into its body - the old castle, by means of threads it had stretched out itself.

In addition, the threads would invade their cranial nerves and give them nightmares. The nightmares were so bad that it was disgusting just to imagine being endlessly shown what each of them dreaded the most.
The nightmares break the hearts and minds of their captives, disabling their conscious and unconscious self-defence functions and squeezing the life force out of them endlessly.
All of this is speculation, assembled by the erudite Fussen from her knowledge of literature, which she had stored away within the depths of her memory...
It is fortunate that no one lost their lives or their minds - For the time being, everyone who was captured by such a terrifying monster was able to reunite safely.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Hmmhmm, I work out! Both in mind and body!

Name: Putra
Phrase: Well, it's not entirely without damage, but... I'm sure I'll be feeling depressed for a while.

Name: Putra
Phrase: I had a very gruesome nightmare... I was being chased around endlessly by some bloody uncle, and there were cut body parts everywhere I went. Bleh, I don't want to remember it.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: You sure can't deal with grotesque stuff, Putra. I feel the same way~ All my good friends around me were brainwashed into some kind of dubious religion, and we were forced to go through some creepy rituals together.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Ooooh~ you two can't handle criminal stuff, Yoshino was locked up in a tight box for a long time... Cried and screamed and there was no response, it was scary.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Ugh, that sounds hard too... I don't like a series of gross or creepy things, but 'nothing at all' is another kind of scary thing.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yeah, it was like despair no matter how hard you try... What about Queensway, what's scary for Queensway? Can't really imagine it, how very curious.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Mm-hm! You should say it, Queensway~ you should confess~!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Why are you doing that, seaweed? In my case usually, I don't like slimy creatures... Like Yoshino, I was trapped in a box, but there were countless snakes, frogs and worms in it--

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Uwaaagh, that might not be possible for me either! Sorry, let's not talk about this! We should be talking about other fun things instead, oui oui♪

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Um - I haven't announced the contents of my dream yet, may I!?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Huh, you're eager to announce it, Paddington, you're such a confusing little girl sometimes...? Oh for goodness sake, let's just forget all about it and pretend dogs had bit us!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Yes... We've already had an accident that interrupted our original mission, talk about getting kicked while down. If it hadn't been for our compatriots from Eisengrad, I don't know what would have happened now.

Name: Fussen
Phrase: Hmmhmm. It is the duty of the nobility to be charitable to the foolish peasants once in a while, praise me more♪

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: Hehehe, I'm glad I was able to [Help] you all...♪

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Hmm. Yes, I'm really glad we were able to save everyone.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: ? Has your mood sort of changed a bit? - Miss Yakutsk?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Really? Are you still half-asleep, Queensway...? I'm always myself♪

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Hmmm~? But normally you'd be just like Miss Fussen there, declaring - 'Of course, for I'm the Great Yakutsk♪' or some other grandstanding, right?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: What, are you trying to say that... I'm just like her? Say that again, and we won't be friends anymore, Queensway!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Heheh. I'm just making light of it because I trust you won't break up with me on something like this.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Once again. Thank you... Miss Yakutsk. For saving us from our nightmares.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: H-Hmph! You're so teary, isn't it natural to help friends after all?

Name: Putra
Phrase: FRIENDS! You finally called us that! I've been waiting for you to say that for a long time, Yakutsk~ Thank you, love you! Kiss, kiss♪

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Woii, you're not my friend yet! If ya want to be called my friend, then don't do anything I don't like! You need to step it up a notch, you're so clingy and bothersome!

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: Hmm. The [Permafrost] will melt someday too, sis... Nice huh♪

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: ...Huh?

Name: Fussen
Phrase: ? What's wrong, klein Murmansk?

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: Nu-uh... Maybe it was just my [Imagination]. I've been [Nervous] for a long time, so I think my alertness is [Heightened].

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: (I wonder what it is... It's something much scarier and more powerful than that horrid [Spider Monster]...)

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: (Was it staring at us? I guess it's just my [Imagination] - everything's been [Resolved] now and there's no need to be [Afraid] of anything, right?)

Name: Murmansk
Phrase: （The [Nightmare] is over, right?)

Name: Resistance
Phrase: That was a waste of time. We rushed over when we sensed a huge amount of magic - but it seems that what was at the bottom of that crevice was merely a monster that has existed for a long time.

Name: Resistance
Phrase: It was a powerful being, but it was no Steel Seeker. It seems that the SSS attacked it and almost neutralised it, so there is no need for us to go to the trouble of devoting our forces to deal with it.
No. Let's take care of them properly. Vermin must be destroyed... Yes?

Name: Resistance
Phrase: Sigh... If that is your order, we will obey. For the future of this world.

The future is irrelevant. Rather, it's about the past - once upon a time, I didn't like insects and various other things, only because I was scared of them... 'That person' once got rid of the insects away from me.
That favour, that memory, is worth repaying in full - even if it drains the strength of the Resistance. Don't you agree?

Name: Resistance
Phrase: No... Um, I'm not sure, to be honest.
I bet... Hmhm, hmmhmmhmm♪ but I'm glad, she's surrounded by her beloved friends - she's smiling happily.
Just seeing dearest sister like that, this time, was not a wasted trip.

Name: Resistance
Phrase: I'm glad you are satisfied, Lady Bestyakh.
The mysterious girl called Bestyakh didn't respond in return... She continued to look endearingly at Yakutsk, who was smiling happily by the train.

Name: Bestyakh
Phrase: Mhmhm. You should be laughing happily now, dearest sister.

Name: Bestyakh
Phrase: Only by cruelly taking away that smile, that happiness from you - that I will have my revenge.
With that soliloquy, she disappeared into the blizzard.
